   {
      "body" : "@GildedHonour Yes they are deprecated in favor of the new option rpcauth, which is the alternative to the default behavior of using a cookie file.\r\n\r\n```\r\n  -rpcauth=<userpw>\r\n       Username and hashed password for JSON-RPC connections. The field\r\n       <userpw> comes in the format: <USERNAME>:<SALT>$<HASH>. A\r\n       canonical python script is included in share/rpcuser. The client\r\n       then connects normally using the\r\n       rpcuser=<USERNAME>/rpcpassword=<PASSWORD> pair of arguments. This\r\n       option can be specified multiple times",
      "created_at" : "2017-04-16T09:57:29Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/10218#issuecomment-294343490",
      "id" : 294343490,
      "issue_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/10218",
