   {
      "body" : "You have three options:\n* Set rpcuser and rpcpassword in bitcoin.conf. If you do that, you must pass that username and password as auth info in curl.\n* Set one or more rpcauth lines in bitcoin.conf. If you do that, you must pass one of those username/password pairs in curl.\n* Don't configure anything in bitcoin.conf. In that case, bitcoind will generate an authentication cookie for you, and write a username/password pair into the .cookie file. You must use the information in that file when connecting via curl.",
      "created_at" : "2017-04-16T10:21:27Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/10218#issuecomment-294344400",
